23 Section 7. That § 32-9-3.1 be AMENDED:
24 32-9-3.1. Any motor vehicle or trailer owned and operated by a resident or a
25 nonresident engaged in the harvest of agricultural products may be operated upon the
26 highways, roads, and streets of this state upon payment of a seventy-five dollar fee.
27 Payment of the fee is evidenced by a permit provided by the department affixed in a
28 conspicuous place on the vehicle as the department may require.
29 Each permit, which is valid for a calendar year, must be purchased from the county
30 treasurer of any county through which the owner or operator may travel, or from an agent,
Underscores indicate new language.
