1034B 3 1034
1 patrol officer, motor carrier enforcement officer, or motor carrier inspector of the
2 Department of Public Safety. If the applicant requests that the permit be mailed, the
3 applicant must pay one dollar two dollars and fifty cents per permit sent to the owner
4 through the mail. All fees collected shall be handled, accounted for, and distributed in the
5 same manner as the other fees provided for in this chapter. A violation of this section is a
6 Class 2 misdemeanor.
7 Section 8. That § 32-9-7 be AMENDED:
8 32-9-7. On receipt of an application under § 32-9-6 and payment of the
9 commercial motor vehicle fee, required by this chapter, and upon satisfactory evidence
10 that the applicant has complied with all laws, rules, and regulations of this state covering
11 motor vehicles and motor carriers, the county treasurer or department shall issue to the
12 applicant a receipt that identifies the motor vehicle, trailer, or semitrailer and shall assign
13 a number to the vehicle. The number shall be endorsed upon the application and receipt.
14 The county treasurer or department shall issue to the applicant a commercial motor
15 vehicle certificate bearing the number. The certificate shall be placed and carried in the
16 vehicle in a conspicuous place and is subject to examination upon demand by any officer
17 of this state, county, or municipality. The county treasurer or department shall issue to
18 the applicant two commercial motor vehicle plates for each motor vehicle. Each county
19 treasurer office shall be stocked with commercial license plates issued pursuant to this
20 section and commercial trailer license plates issued pursuant to § 32-9-8.1.
21 If the plates are mailed, the applicant must pay seven twelve dollars and fifty cents
22 per license plate or set of plates if the plate is sent to the owner through the mail, or one
23 dollar two dollars and fifty cents per decal or set of decals if the decal is sent to the owner
24 through the mail. If the applicant requests that the plate or decal be express mailed, the
25 applicant must pay any costs for the express mailing service.
26 Each plate must set forth the amount of gross weight in figures, and be in colors
27 and designs for each classification specified in § 32-9-15. Each plate must be securely
28 fastened to the front and rear end of each commercial motor vehicle in a conspicuous
29 place.
30 The county treasurer shall deposit in the county general fund any fees received for
31 mailing or expressing a plate or sticker. The department shall deposit all fees received for
32 mailing or expressing the plates or stickers in the state motor vehicle fund. A violation of
33 this section is a Class 2 misdemeanor.
