1 Section 9. That § 32-10-17 be AMENDED:
2 32-10-17. The administrator shall register the vehicles described and identified in
3 an application pursuant to § 32-10-15 and shall issue a license plate or plates, or a vehicle
4 registration card, or other suitable identification device, for each vehicle described in the
5 application upon payment of the fees for registration and licensing and for the vehicle
6 registration cards or other identification devices. A fee of three dollars must be paid for
7 each card or device issued for each proportionally registered vehicle. The card must, in
8 addition to the information required by chapter 32-5, identify the number of the license
9 or other device issued for the proportionally registered vehicle and must be carried in the
10 vehicle at all times or, in the case of a combination, in the vehicle supplying the motive
11 power. For purposes of this section, the operator may provide proof in either paper or
12 electronic format including a display of an electronic image on an electronic device.
13 In addition to the registration fees, the department shall collect from charge the
14 owner seven dollars and fifty cents, when sent to the owner through the mail:
15 (1) Twelve dollars per license plate or set of plates when a plate is sent to the owner
16 through the mail, or one dollar; and
17 (2) Two dollars and fifty cents per decal or set of decals if a decal is sent to the owner
18 through the mail.
19 If the applicant requests that the plate or decal be express mailed, the applicant
20 must pay any costs for the express mailing service.
